<PageLayout
  title="About RangeTube"
  description="RangeTube is a free, backendless tool to loop a chosen section of any YouTube video — for music practice, language learning, dance, and study."
>
  <h1>About RangeTube</h1>
  <p>
    RangeTube is a free tool that loops a chosen section of any YouTube video. Paste a link, set a
    start and end point, and that range repeats endlessly — handy for practising a passage of music,
    shadowing a language, drilling a dance move, or reviewing part of a lecture.
  </p>
  <p>
    It runs entirely in your browser. There is no account, no backend, and no database. Videos are
    played through YouTube's official embeddable player; RangeTube only sends the player commands
    (seek and loop). It never downloads, stores, or hosts any video.
  </p>
  <p>
    RangeTube is an independent project built as part of <a href="https://salvarecuero.dev">a
    developer portfolio</a>. See the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> and
    <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> for details, or <a href="/">try the tool</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
